            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Most of the time I'd expect to find a `dune-project` or `.git`, it'd be very rare for a project to have neither.\r\n`*.opam` should be future-proof though, once neovim supports it then it'll start working (until then I assume it'd match just a literal `*.opam` file).\r\n\r\nHowever I've added `opam`, some projects have either an `opam` file at their root (very simple ones that only define one `opam` project), or an `opam` directory (containing all the `*.opam` files), and this one should work without wildcards.",
            "commit_id": "9be62d00683c770da2ed7fc5921e15cdbf9a4216",
            "created_at": "2025-09-24T23:06:49Z",
